name: La ribonucleoprotein 4
summary: Enables mRNA 3'-UTR binding activity and poly(A) binding activity. Involved in cytoskeleton organization; positive regulation of translation; and regulation of cell morphogenesis. Located in cytosol. Colocalizes with cytoplasmic stress granule; cytosolic small ribosomal subunit; and polysome. [provided by Alliance of Genome Resources, Apr 2022]
